# task #134: the client menu's "Tailscale: Reconnect" row (beside status/reset) reports the
# lib's honest success token as "Reconnected (<ip>)". Lib restart logic itself is covered by
# the t-ts-reconnect-* tslib scenarios; this pins the row + UX text + dispatch.
desc menu: Tailscale: Reconnect row -> "Reconnected (100.64.0.9)" on success
config paired
seeded
ts present
tsstatus connected
pick 0|Tailscale: Reconnect
pick 2|
expect_exit 0
expect_trace TESTLIB tailscale_reconnect (scripted status=connected)
expect_trace PRES timeout=-1 msg='Reconnecting Tailscale...'
expect_trace PRES timeout=5 msg='Reconnected (100.64.0.9)'
